    <!-- Practical exercise -->
    <h2>Practical exercise - <span class="keyword">Mini DVC pipeline</span></h2>

    <div class="quest-objective">
      <p>Create a mini data science project with DVC. You'll initialize a repository, add a dataset, and create a simple processing pipeline.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 1 - Initialize the project</h3>

    <pre data-lang="bash"><code># Create the project
mkdir infinite-archives-project
cd infinite-archives-project
git init
dvc init

# Create the structure
mkdir -p data/raw data/processed src models metrics

# Commit the initialization
git add .
git commit -m "Initialize project with Git and DVC"</code></pre>

    <pre data-lang="powershell"><code># Create the project
mkdir infinite-archives-project
cd infinite-archives-project
git init
dvc init

# Create the structure
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path data/raw, data/processed, src, models, metrics

# Commit the initialization
git add .
git commit -m "Initialize project with Git and DVC"</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 2 - Create a fictional dataset</h3>

    <pre data-lang="bash"><code># Create a small fictional CSV dataset
cat > data/raw/adventurers.csv << 'EOF'
name,class,level,strength,intelligence,xp
